---
description: Flag OWASP Top 10 patterns and secrets in generated or modified code
alwaysApply: true
---

When generating or modifying code in this workspace:

- Never hardcode secrets, API keys, tokens, passwords, or connection strings. Use environment variables or secret managers.
- Sanitize all user inputs before passing to SQL queries, shell commands, HTML templates, or eval-like constructs.
- Use parameterized queries for all database operations — never string-concatenate user input into SQL.
- Validate and escape output rendered in HTML to prevent XSS.
- Check authentication and authorization on every endpoint, not just at the router level.
- Prefer allowlists over denylists for input validation.
- Flag any use of `eval()`, `exec()`, `Function()`, `child_process.exec()` with unsanitized input.
- When adding dependencies, check for known CVEs. Prefer actively maintained packages.
- Log security-relevant events (auth failures, permission denials) without logging sensitive data.
